observations.managementAction:
1. The Inventory Committee will prepare the Physical Inventory Plan on time and will conduct complete physical count of PPE;
2. The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Engineer will provide the necessary documents as the basis of General Services Officer in recording and updating of PPE Property Cards;
3. The General Services Officer will update immediately all PCs upon receipt of the RPCPPE;
4. The GSO shall provide complete listing of property counted to enable the Accounting Department to analyze and reconcile the discrepancies and to make the necessary adjusting entries in the books of accounts; and
5. The Inventory Committee, Municipal Accountant, Municipal Engineer and General Services Officer committed to comply with the recommendations of the Audit Team.

observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the:

a. Municipal Accountant to record all purchases of supplies and materials under the appropriate inventory account and to recognize expense only when the items are already consumed based on the SSMI submitted by the OIC-GSO; 

b. Municipal Accountant and the OIC-GSO to maintain SLC and SC, respectively, for each commodity/stock;

c. OIC-GSO to prepare RIS for issuances of supplies and materials and consolidate them on a weekly basis using the SSMI and furnish the Municipal Accountant with copies thereof for recording in the books of the cost of issued items; and

d. OIC-GSO to conduct physical count of inventories semi-annually and to prepare and submit the Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI) to the Auditor not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year.
